{{#if isNestJS}}
All database access goes through `[feature].repository.ts`.
Services **never** import `{{ormServiceName}}` directly. This encapsulates the data layer and enables easier mocking in tests.

**Implementation:**
- Inject `{{ormServiceName}}` into your repository class.
- Provide repositories in the feature module.
- Services inject the repository, never `{{ormServiceName}}`.
{{else if isExpress}}
All database access goes through `{feature}.repository.ts`.
Controllers **never** import `{{ormServiceName}}` directly.

**Implementation:**
- Pass the `{{ormServiceName}}` to repository constructors or use a DI container.
- Controllers call service methods, and services call repository methods.
{{else if isFastify}}
All database access goes through `{feature}.repository.ts`.
Route handlers **never** import the database instance directly.

**Implementation:**
- Decorate the fastify instance with your repositories or use a DI container.
- Services/handlers use `fastify.repositories.feature` instead of raw queries.
{{else if isHono}}
All database access goes through `{feature}.repository.ts`.
Route handlers **never** import the database instance directly.
{{/if}}
